modules.description: This module implements a data structure that stores elements in reverse order, providing functions for binary serialization, deserialization, comparison, S-expression conversion, and mapping over the contained values. It supports operations like `map`, `compare`, and bidirectional conversion to and from binary and S-expression formats. Concrete use cases include efficiently storing and transmitting reversed sequences while preserving type stability and enabling direct binary manipulation.

This module implements a type-stable reversed storage structure with support for binary serialization, deserialization, S-expression conversion, and value mapping. It provides concrete operations including `map`, `compare`, and format conversions, working directly with reversed sequences. Use cases include efficient transmission and storage of reversed data with guaranteed type stability and direct binary manipulation.
